"{\"uid\": \"nationaltribune.com.au-anatomy-of-a-wave-what-makes-the-olympic-surf-break-at-teahupo-o-unique-and-so-challenging\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"As the Olympics get going in earnest this week, not everyone's attention is focused on host city Paris.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 103, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 97, \"end\": 102, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999998834650111, \"rank\": 1.1653514643765623e-06, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Surf fans are heading to Tahiti, half a world away in French Polynesia.\", \"from\": 104, \"to\": 175, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 129, \"end\": 135, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.9960207649649105, \"rank\": 0.0039951326065843845, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}, {\"begin\": 165, \"end\": 174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.9275893760723684, \"rank\": 0.07806323120476796, \"text\": \"Polynesia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tom Shand  Honorary Senior Lecturer, Department of Civil and Environmental Engineering, University of Auckland, Waipapa Taumata Rau  Why?\", \"from\": 177, \"to\": 314, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 177, \"end\": 186, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Shand\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Shand\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Shand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Shand\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Well, apart from the French coast resembling a lake at this time of year, on the south-west coast of Tahiti Iti is a wave unlike any other on the planet: Teahupo'o, which translates somewhat ominously as \\\"place of skulls\\\".\", \"from\": 315, \"to\": 537, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 336, \"end\": 342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9965653737785576, \"rank\": 0.0030123565875588903, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The wave is unique in the way it breaks.\", \"from\": 539, \"to\": 579, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The lower part of the wave appears to drop away below sea level, with the top half folding over dramatically to create an almost cartoonishly perfect form.\", \"from\": 580, \"to\": 735, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is both the weight of water in the plunging lip and the risk of injury or death for a surfer in the wrong position that make this one of the world's heaviest waves (in both senses of the word).\", \"from\": 737, \"to\": 933, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"To understand why the wave breaks like this, we need to start withbathymetry: the shape of the seabed that influences waves as they approach the shore.\", \"from\": 935, \"to\": 1086, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At Teahupo'o, acombination of factorscomes into play.\", \"from\": 1087, \"to\": 1140, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Waves arriving at Teahupo'o generally originate from intense \\\"roaring forties\\\" storm systems south of New Zealand.\", \"from\": 1142, \"to\": 1256, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1244, \"end\": 1255, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealanders\", \"score\": 0.5446388060416224, \"rank\": 0.4990404841439279, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealanders\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealanders\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By the time the waves reach Tahiti they have become ordered swell, with wave heights of two to five metres and periods of 14 to 20 seconds between successive waves.\", \"from\": 1257, \"to\": 1421, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1285, \"end\": 1291, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.9960207649649105, \"rank\": 0.0039951326065843845, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These types of long-period waves normally start interacting with the seabed at depths of around 200 metres.\", \"from\": 1423, \"to\": 1530, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On most coasts, this depth would occur up to several kilometres offshore.\", \"from\": 1531, \"to\": 1604, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But at Teahupo'o, it is much closer, just a couple of hundred metres.\", \"from\": 1605, \"to\": 1674, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This rapid change in depth forces the wave to \\\"shoal\\\" very quickly - the wave speed slows, the distance between waves compresses and the wave height increases.\", \"from\": 1676, \"to\": 1835, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The change is so abrupt that the wave is still very linear - it has not had time to develop the peaked crest and flat trough (the lowest part of the wave) typical of waves in shallow water.\", \"from\": 1837, \"to\": 2026, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Waves breaking on this type of steep slope would typically collapse, breaking from the middle of the wave and creating an unsurfable mess.\", \"from\": 2028, \"to\": 2166, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But this does not happen.\", \"from\": 2167, \"to\": 2192, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At around ten metres' depth, a flatter shelf in the reef allows the wave to stabilise and \\\"stand up\\\" with a steep front face, before finally breaking as the reef rises again.\", \"from\": 2194, \"to\": 2368, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And break it does.\", \"from\": 2370, \"to\": 2388, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Owing to the linearity, there is far more water in the crest (the part above water) then most waves, and a deeper trough in front.\", \"from\": 2389, \"to\": 2519, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This makes for the characteristic below-sea-level break at Teahupo'o, with the overturning lip being half the wave height, and a jet of compressed air forced out of the wave's barrel after breaking.\", \"from\": 2521, \"to\": 2719, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The larger the wave, the closer to the steep offshore ramp it breaks, and the more extreme the plunging.\", \"from\": 2721, \"to\": 2825, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A range of other unique features contribute to the way the wave breaks at Teahupo'o - and what makes it so challenging as a surfing wave.\", \"from\": 2827, \"to\": 2964, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A deep channel runs alongside the shallow reef shelf.\", \"from\": 2966, \"to\": 3019, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The wave does not break in this deeper area, allowing it to peel - to break in one direction (in this case towards the left looking towards the shore) - and enabling surfers to ride the wave before it finally closes out onto shallow reef.\", \"from\": 3020, \"to\": 3258, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A part of the shallow reef platform extends offshore, into the reef pass.\", \"from\": 3260, \"to\": 3333, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This shallow area bends and focuses wave energy from the wider, deeper part of the wave back into the breaking wave.\", \"from\": 3334, \"to\": 3450, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This happens particularly on more westerly orientated swells, increasing the intensity of breaking.\", \"from\": 3451, \"to\": 3550, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As well as this, the Teahupo'o wave breaks in a direction nearly opposite to the prevailing trade winds, keeping the wave face smooth.\", \"from\": 3552, \"to\": 3686, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A low tidal range also limits the times the reef is too deep or too shallow to surf.\", \"from\": 3688, \"to\": 3772, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And the wave is near the Passa Hava'e reef pass, which helps the wave's focusing and breaking.\", \"from\": 3773, \"to\": 3867, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3798, \"end\": 3803, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Passa,_Pyr\\u00e9n\\u00e9es-Orientales\", \"score\": 0.9999999954807208, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Passa\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Passa,_Pyr\\u00e9n\\u00e9es-Orientales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Passa,_Pyr\\u00e9n\\u00e9es-Orientales\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But because it is not right in the pass, the wave is not affected by high tidal or wave-induced currents.\", \"from\": 3868, \"to\": 3973, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"New-generation wave models that simulate individual waves, rather than just average energy density, provide insight into what creates a surf break such as Teahupo'o (see figure below).\", \"from\": 3975, \"to\": 4159, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These models provide insight into what happens as waves shoal and refract (bend and focus) over the seabed as they approach break point.\", \"from\": 4160, \"to\": 4296, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They also significantly improve our understanding of what makes a particular surf break unique.\", \"from\": 4298, \"to\": 4393, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This can help in assessing the potential impact of human or natural modifications to the environment.\", \"from\": 4394, \"to\": 4495, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tom Shand is affiliated with the Engineering Consultancy Tonkin + Taylor and with the industry association PIANC (World Association for Waterborne Transport Infrastructure).\", \"from\": 4499, \"to\": 4672, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4499, \"end\": 4508, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Shand\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Shand\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Shand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Shand\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"3 Dec 2025 5:06 am AEST  3 Dec 2025 5:06 am AEST  3 Dec 2025 5:06 am AEST  3 Dec 2025 4:45 am AEST  3 Dec 2025 4:42 am AEST  3 Dec 2025 4:42 am AEST  3 Dec 2025 4:33 am AEST  3 Dec 2025 4:30 am AEST  3 Dec 2025 4:03 am AEST  3 Dec 2025 3:54 am AEST  3 Dec 2025 3:48 am AEST  3 Dec 2025 3:45 am AEST  3 Dec 2025 3:39 am AEST  3 Dec 2025 3:24 am AEST  3 Dec 2025 3:09 am AEST  3 Dec 2025 2:15 am AEST  3 Dec 2025 1:57 am AEST  3 Dec 2025 1:48 am AEST  3 Dec 2025 1:30 am AEST  3 Dec 2025 1:27 am AEST  3 Dec 2025 1:21 am AEST  3 Dec 2025 1:15 am AEST  3 Dec 2025 12:48 am AEST  3 Dec 2025 12:16 am AEST  3 Dec 2025 12:15 am AEST  3 Dec 2025 12:15 am AEST  3 Dec 2025 12:12 am AEST  3 Dec 2025 12:12 am AEST  Based in Toowoomba QLD, The National Tribune provides 24/7 free live coverage of important events and developments in Australia and the Pacific region leveraging real-time open-source intelligence.\", \"from\": 4674, \"to\": 5577, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4693, \"end\": 4697, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Time_in_Australia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"AEST\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Time_in_Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Time_in_Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 4718, \"end\": 4722, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Time_in_Australia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"AEST\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Time_in_Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Time_in_Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 4743, \"end\": 4747, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Time_in_Australia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"AEST\", \"types\": [], \"wiki